http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 5 Sep 2017
Source: OIE, WAHID [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=24732


Foot-and-mouth disease, Malawi
--------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 5 Sep 2017 from Dr Bernard Chimera, Director of Veterinary Services, Department of Animal Health & Livestock Development, Ministry of Agriculture and Food Security, Lilongwe, Malawi

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 24 Aug 2017
Date of confirmation of the event: 30 Aug 2017
Reason for notification: recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 25 Mar 2017
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: foot-and-mouth disease virus
Serotype: pending
Nature of diagnosis: suspicion, clinical
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1 (MWI/FMD/2017/1): Mthumba Dip Tank, T/A Katunga, Chikwawa
Date of start of the outbreak: 24 Aug 2017
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: other
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 30 000 / 26 / 0 / 0 / 0

Affected population: The affected population is under a communal grazing system and in very close proximity to buffaloes that are in Lengwe National Park. There is occasional mixing of cattle and buffaloes, especially when the buffaloes stray out of the park and graze with cattle. The population is within the locality that is strategically vaccinated against FMD using a trivalent FMD vaccine containing the 3 SAT strains (SAT1, SAT2 and SAT3).

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 0.09 / 0 / 0 / 0
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: There is a strong suspicion that it originated from buffaloes found in Lengwe National Park, which occasionally mix with cattle in the area.

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country, surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone, surveillance within containment and/or protection zone, quarantine, control of wildlife reservoirs, disinfection, process to inactivate the pathogenic agent in products or by-products, vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists), no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: vaccination in response to the outbreak(s), screening, traceability, official destruction of animal products

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Malawi Central Veterinary Laboratory (National laboratory) / Cattle / ELISA 3ABC / - / Pending

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The previous FMD event was reported on 30 Aug 2015, where the serotype SAT1 was identified in 2 outbreaks; these were located in the districts of Chikwawa and Nsanje. The event was resolved on 25 Mar 2016. See a summary and updated map of this event at: http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?reportid=18698.

Chikwawa is a district in the southern region of Malawi https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chikwawa_District. A map of Malawi can be seen at http://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/map/malawi_map.htm. - Mod.CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5297152,8665.]
